01:51.946 --> 01:54.781
<i>Last time I saw all this,</i>

01:54.782 --> 02:00.327
<i>I think it's fair to say I was
at a turning point in my life.</i>

02:00.328 --> 02:05.708
<i>I promised some people I'd
come back, and I am back.</i>

02:05.709 --> 02:08.794
<i>My life has changed a lot.</i>

02:08.795 --> 02:12.841
<i>How much have their lives changed?</i>

02:24.019 --> 02:27.063
<i>Kuala Lumpur.</i>

02:27.064 --> 02:30.817
<i>Happy to be here, but
brimming with mixed emotions.</i>

02:30.818 --> 02:32.485
<i>Surrounded by all the sights,</i>

02:32.486 --> 02:36.782
<i>smells, and flavors I remember so well.</i>

02:44.623 --> 02:47.416
<i>This is where a wandering
soul such as myself</i>

02:47.417 --> 02:50.920
<i>can dive right in and get some
of that straight Chinese food</i>

02:50.921 --> 02:54.090
<i>I've been missing.</i>

02:54.091 --> 02:57.010
First order of business, dinner.

02:57.011 --> 03:02.723
Been on a plane for, like,
I don't know, it was long.

03:02.724 --> 03:05.852
Very long.

03:05.853 --> 03:10.023
Saw, like, five Mark Wahlberg films.

03:10.024 --> 03:12.108
I can't tell you how excited
I am about the prospect

03:12.109 --> 03:15.361
of getting some black pepper crab...

03:15.362 --> 03:19.282
and some pork gladed noodles
and a regional beverage.

03:22.703 --> 03:23.996
Reasonably cold.

03:25.204 --> 03:27.749
I don't even know what this is.

03:29.584 --> 03:31.335
I love you, noodles.

03:31.336 --> 03:34.505
Don't want to get all heavy and
philosophical at this point,

03:34.506 --> 03:36.924
but why I'm here, what my mission is,

03:36.925 --> 03:38.843
what I expect to find,

03:38.844 --> 03:42.096
basically me tracing my steps and all that.

03:42.097 --> 03:44.850
We'll talk about that later.
Right now, noodles.

03:47.811 --> 03:49.145
Good.

03:49.146 --> 03:51.189
This place is most excellent.

03:51.190 --> 03:53.524
Ah, char kuey teow. Char kuey teow.

03:53.525 --> 03:55.401
Char kuey teow, bitches.

03:55.402 --> 04:00.698
Oh, look at the greasy,
fatty, yes, come to daddy.

04:00.699 --> 04:03.450
I'm a bad man.

04:03.451 --> 04:05.870
This is, like, a random restaurant,

04:05.871 --> 04:08.873
with like a purloined Minnie Mouse logo

04:08.874 --> 04:12.292
and their food is unbelievably good.

04:12.293 --> 04:14.754
Oh, yeah. Black pepper crab.

04:14.755 --> 04:18.548
Right here. Reveal yourself to me.

04:18.550 --> 04:20.718
Hot, hot, hot.

04:20.719 --> 04:23.055
Ooh! Oh, yeah.

04:26.307 --> 04:29.435
Wow.

04:29.436 --> 04:32.939
All right. The frenzy's over.

04:32.940 --> 04:36.110
Now to eat in a more relaxed phase.

04:51.541 --> 04:57.255
<i>Kuala Lumpur rises up out of
steamy, equatorial jungle,</i>

04:57.256 --> 04:59.673
<i>Malaysia's capital city.</i>

04:59.674 --> 05:02.718
<i>A chaotic, multi-ethnic, multi-cultural</i>

05:02.719 --> 05:10.517
<i>modern metropolis of
Malay, Chinese and Indian.</i>

05:10.518 --> 05:14.064
<i>- This is where you start out when
fulfilling a decade-old - promise</i>

05:14.067 --> 05:15.898
<i>To your ex-headhunter friends</i>

05:15.899 --> 05:20.236
<i>to return for Gawai, the annual
Iban rice harvest festival.</i>

05:20.237 --> 05:22.404
What's interesting the
last time I was there was

05:22.405 --> 05:26.867
the old guys with their tattoos
and rings on their fingers.

05:26.868 --> 05:28.744
Yeah, the old people,

05:28.745 --> 05:30.163
a lot of them have passed on.

05:30.164 --> 05:31.872
I hear no more skulls.

05:31.873 --> 05:36.669
They made them put the skulls away.

05:36.670 --> 05:39.337
<i>The Iban once enjoyed a
truly formidable reputation</i>

05:39.338 --> 05:41.007
<i>as trackers, warriors,</i>

05:41.008 --> 05:44.260
<i>and ritualistic takers of heads.</i>

05:44.261 --> 05:47.387
<i>They were and continue to be wanderers.</i>

05:47.388 --> 05:50.474
<i>Valuing a tradition where every tribesman</i>

05:50.475 --> 05:52.434
<i>was set out from the longhouse of his birth</i>

05:52.435 --> 05:56.189
<i>to travel, learn, to bring something back.</i>

05:56.190 --> 05:59.233
<i>Each tattoo he gets over
the course of his life</i>

05:59.234 --> 06:01.568
<i>represents a different experience,</i>

06:01.569 --> 06:03.321
<i>a different journey.</i>

06:03.322 --> 06:06.032
Basically the tattoos signify knowledge

06:06.033 --> 06:08.450
and the wealth they brought
back to the longhouse,

06:08.451 --> 06:12.663
what you probably would want to get is a...

06:12.664 --> 06:13.831
Something like this.

06:13.832 --> 06:16.125
Ah, like that. Yeah.

06:16.126 --> 06:19.628
Since last I saw you, you
were, and you gave me this.

06:19.629 --> 06:22.340
And it's still there. Still there.

06:22.341 --> 06:25.218
<i>Ten years ago at his shop, Borneo Ink,</i>

06:25.219 --> 06:28.762
<i>Eddie David tattooed me with
an Iban style ouroborous.</i>

06:28.763 --> 06:31.389
<i>The symbol of a snake eating its own tail.</i>

06:31.390 --> 06:35.644
<i>Life, death, the eternal ebb and flow.</i>

06:35.645 --> 06:39.106
<i>I think I was going through a hippy phase.</i>

06:39.107 --> 06:40.941
<i>Eddie does great work</i>

06:40.942 --> 06:43.194
<i>and he's known for
traditional tribal tattoos</i>

06:43.195 --> 06:46.780
<i>but I'm looking forward to
getting it done old school.</i>

06:46.781 --> 06:49.658
<i>Hand tapped in the jungle.</i>

06:49.659 --> 06:51.409
So, I need your advice

06:51.410 --> 06:53.620
because I'm going back to the same village

06:53.621 --> 06:56.749
that I went to last time.

06:56.750 --> 06:59.793
Just be careful of the...

06:59.794 --> 07:01.837
Yes, they had it in every type of bottle.

07:01.838 --> 07:05.049
This is clear sort of cloudy
liquid with particles in it.

07:05.050 --> 07:07.801
Sometimes they put weird stuff inside.

07:07.802 --> 07:10.284
My dad used to tell me
they take mosquito coil

07:10.285 --> 07:12.765
and leave it inside the...

07:12.766 --> 07:13.933
A mosquito what?

07:13.934 --> 07:14.893
Coil.

07:14.894 --> 07:15.935
Like the pesticide?

07:15.936 --> 07:17.144
Yeah.

07:17.145 --> 07:18.771
Just make it, like, stronger.

07:18.772 --> 07:21.899
I would imagine so.

07:21.900 --> 07:23.734
That's a natural staple,

07:23.735 --> 07:28.781
Gawai, usually drinking, passing
out, waking up, eating, drinking

07:28.782 --> 07:33.702
passing out again then getting
up and drinking some more.

07:33.703 --> 07:34.828
Yeah.

07:34.829 --> 07:36.789
You're going to have fun, man.

07:36.790 --> 07:39.208
Wow. All right.

07:39.209 --> 07:42.587
♪

07:55.516 --> 07:58.102
<i>So I'm headed upriver again.</i>

07:58.103 --> 08:01.021
Yeah, sorry I can't be there.

08:01.022 --> 08:02.940
I promised them, I said I'm going back.

08:02.941 --> 08:06.777
About nine years late
on your promise, but...

08:06.778 --> 08:07.654
Nine years late.

08:07.655 --> 08:09.280
That happens.

08:09.281 --> 08:11.157
You know, promises come liberally.

08:11.158 --> 08:14.660
<i>It was David Moggie who first
took me up to the longhouse.</i>

08:14.661 --> 08:17.496
<i>On that previous trip
we met at Aunty Aini's</i>

08:17.497 --> 08:21.583
<i>on the outskirts of KL.</i>

08:21.584 --> 08:24.462
Everything moves exponentially.

08:24.463 --> 08:27.047
Feels like some things
remain exactly the same,

08:27.048 --> 08:28.924
some things haven't changed at all.

08:28.925 --> 08:31.303
This place is certainly one.

08:34.554 --> 08:38.267
<i>The charming and for lack of
a better word fabulous Aini,</i>

08:38.268 --> 08:40.977
<i>was an actor in the Malaysian film scene</i>

08:40.979 --> 08:44.357
<i>who now runs a very successful
kampong style restaurant</i>

08:44.358 --> 08:48.735
<i>specializing in beloved
village or country classics.</i>

08:48.736 --> 08:50.196
<i>All of them prepared</i>

08:50.197 --> 08:52.656
<i>with a staggering finesse and precision.</i>

08:52.657 --> 08:56.495
<i>This is delicious, delicious food.</i>

08:57.412 --> 08:58.954
Welcome.

08:58.955 --> 09:01.957
It's been so long. Oh, my God.

09:01.958 --> 09:06.086
And you still look as handsome as ever.

09:06.087 --> 09:07.963
All right.

09:07.964 --> 09:10.299
Well, let's pick up right
where we left off,

09:10.300 --> 09:12.051
which started with this.

09:12.052 --> 09:13.052
Help yourself.

09:13.053 --> 09:14.761
Thank you.

09:14.762 --> 09:20.726
You're going to have the
roast beef and poached egg

09:20.727 --> 09:25.731
and our favorite will
be our chicken rendang.

09:25.732 --> 09:28.775
So good to be back.

09:28.776 --> 09:32.571
I love watching you guys eat.

09:32.572 --> 09:33.864
Who taught you to cook?

09:33.865 --> 09:35.908
Who was the good cook in your family?

09:35.909 --> 09:37.701
When we were small,

09:37.702 --> 09:40.913
my grandmother would say stuff
like, I don't care who you are,

09:40.914 --> 09:44.333
if you can't cook, you're nobody to me.

09:44.334 --> 09:46.001
- Oh, wow.
- Yeah.

09:46.002 --> 09:48.546
There's no teaching Malay cooking here.

09:48.547 --> 09:51.924
It comes from your grandma's
kitchen, your mom's kitchen.

09:51.925 --> 09:56.803
And you learn by smelling, by seeing...

09:56.804 --> 09:59.390
<i>It's how I teach my children to cook.</i>

09:59.391 --> 10:02.351
<i>All these dishes, when you do them,</i>

10:02.352 --> 10:04.811
<i>the aroma just floats around.</i>

10:04.812 --> 10:08.441
<i>I know exactly when the chili paste</i>

10:08.442 --> 10:11.110
<i>frying in the pan is ready or not.</i>

10:11.111 --> 10:12.570
It's from here.

10:12.571 --> 10:14.573
Basically it's from here.

10:24.999 --> 10:28.168
<i>After a two-hour flight from
Kuala Lumpur, I land in Borneo,</i>

10:28.169 --> 10:31.422
<i>third largest island in the world.</i>

10:31.423 --> 10:36.469
<i>Divided between Malaysia,
Brunei, and Indonesia.</i>

10:36.470 --> 10:39.846
<i>Kuching, capital of the Malaysian Sarawak.</i>

10:39.847 --> 10:44.351
<i>It's a sleepy city with
a colorful 19th century</i>

10:44.352 --> 10:46.312
<i>boys' adventure story history.</i>

10:46.313 --> 10:49.648
<i>Pirates, headhunters, opportunists.</i>

10:49.649 --> 10:52.276
<i>The former domain of Sir James Brooke,</i>

10:52.277 --> 10:56.071
<i>an Englishman who came to
be known as the White Raja.</i>

10:56.072 --> 10:59.199
<i>For a century, generations
of the Brook family</i>

10:59.200 --> 11:02.495
<i>ruled Sarawak as an independent kingdom.</i>

11:02.496 --> 11:05.498
<i>They created their own
army, the Sarawak Rangers</i>

11:05.499 --> 11:09.918
<i>who also acted as the
Raja's personal guard.</i>

11:09.919 --> 11:13.422
<i>Tomorrow I follow the
pavement as far as it goes,</i>

11:13.423 --> 11:15.882
<i>then it's boats the rest of the way.</i>

11:15.883 --> 11:18.385
<i>But first, breakfast.</i>

11:18.386 --> 11:21.515
<i>And fortunately, I know
exactly where to go.</i>

11:24.267 --> 11:26.394
I sat at this same table last time.

11:28.313 --> 11:35.110
If I look at my life as a
continuum, a trail of noodles,

11:35.111 --> 11:37.029
going round and round the world

11:37.030 --> 11:42.576
until it comes right back
to the same spicy bowl.

11:42.577 --> 11:45.412
Oh, yeah.

11:45.413 --> 11:49.041
That is... can I say tumescent on CNN?

11:49.042 --> 11:52.086
Yeah, I'm pretty sure I can.

11:55.173 --> 11:57.424
Oh, yeah, baby.

11:57.425 --> 11:59.385
This is a magical dish.

11:59.386 --> 12:01.761
I don't know. It's two
types of noodles, I think.

12:01.762 --> 12:06.475
Chicken, prawn, coconut, chili.

12:06.476 --> 12:09.769
You know, the main event
of this is the broth.

12:09.770 --> 12:12.523
The wisdom of the ages
is contained in there.

12:12.524 --> 12:14.900
It's, like, super complex.

12:14.901 --> 12:17.987
Ooh. Ooh-ooh-ooh.

12:19.489 --> 12:22.866
Might need more of this.

12:22.867 --> 12:23.992
All right.

12:23.993 --> 12:25.494
I'll have another one of these.

12:25.495 --> 12:27.746
More.

12:29.416 --> 12:33.126
It's the broth. The broth.

12:33.127 --> 12:36.214
Look at it.

12:37.882 --> 12:39.425
Thank you.

12:39.426 --> 12:43.095
Now I'm becoming the
object of much amusement.

12:43.096 --> 12:47.015
People have noticed I'm on my second.

12:47.016 --> 12:48.850
Damn.

12:48.851 --> 12:52.063
Best breakfast ever.

13:48.703 --> 13:50.747
Love that sound.

14:14.479 --> 14:17.106
♪

14:22.903 --> 14:27.032
<i>Before heading out to the longhouse,</i>

14:27.033 --> 14:29.201
<i>I'm meeting Kuching native Alex Wong</i>

14:29.202 --> 14:32.996
<i>at a dockside karaoke joint
on the Malay side of town.</i>

14:32.997 --> 14:35.207
What's up with the karaoke here?

14:35.208 --> 14:38.293
It's popular everywhere, but
this is alcohol-free karaoke.

14:38.294 --> 14:40.295
Yes.

14:40.296 --> 14:41.714
In my experience, you got
to be really [ muted ] up

14:41.715 --> 14:44.299
to do karaoke, but here apparently not.

14:44.300 --> 14:46.677
No, no. It's the spirit.

14:46.678 --> 14:49.929
Our people here, they can party any time.

14:49.930 --> 14:53.267
♪

14:57.104 --> 15:01.400
So you're coming upriver with us?

15:01.401 --> 15:03.985
Yes, I am. Exciting.

15:03.986 --> 15:07.447
Four days of non-connectivity.
You know that?

15:07.448 --> 15:08.824
Yes.

15:08.825 --> 15:11.326
I'm committed to that. It's the drinking.

15:11.327 --> 15:13.286
I'm worried about that, too, seriously,

15:13.287 --> 15:16.122
because I'm past my
drinking days, you know?

15:16.123 --> 15:20.085
But I don't think there's
an escape from it.

15:20.086 --> 15:24.339
Why are you back in
Kuching after ten years?

15:24.340 --> 15:27.050
All the places in Borneo?

15:27.051 --> 15:28.343
It's a good question.

15:28.344 --> 15:32.723
Um, I'm revisiting some stuff.

15:32.724 --> 15:35.684
Just some... I was in a
weird place in my head

15:35.685 --> 15:37.060
when I first came here.

15:37.061 --> 15:38.395
I was personally, professionally,

15:38.396 --> 15:40.397
everything in my life was changing.

15:40.398 --> 15:43.650
I was in this sort of nowhere
land between previous life

15:43.651 --> 15:46.194
and whatever came next.

15:46.195 --> 15:48.572
I'm retracing my steps to a lot of this

15:48.573 --> 15:50.657
to see if it still hurts.

15:50.658 --> 15:53.535
Ah, okay.

15:53.536 --> 15:57.163
And also I said I'd promise
these guys in the village,

15:57.164 --> 15:59.999
the chiefs, that I'd come back.

16:00.000 --> 16:02.377
Well, I made a promise, and
I'm going to live up to it.

16:02.378 --> 16:03.546
Yeah.

16:12.179 --> 16:16.684
♪

17:18.913 --> 17:21.790
Even the jungle wanted him dead.

17:34.804 --> 17:37.055
<i>This river, what's the line?</i>

17:37.056 --> 17:39.016
<i>Snakes through the Sarawak jungle</i>

17:39.017 --> 17:40.893
<i>like a main circuit cable,</i>

17:40.894 --> 17:45.104
<i>plugged straight in a, somewhere.</i>

17:45.105 --> 17:47.649
<i>A place.</i>

17:47.650 --> 17:49.401
<i>A state of mind.</i>

17:49.402 --> 17:51.194
<i>I don't know.</i>

17:51.195 --> 17:53.739
<i>I was a basket case last
time I went up this river.</i>

17:53.740 --> 17:58.035
<i>My mind miles away.</i>

17:58.036 --> 18:01.914
Is this how you remember it, Tony?

18:01.915 --> 18:03.331
Yeah.

18:03.332 --> 18:05.083
Exactly the same, huh?

18:05.084 --> 18:07.252
Ten years later? Pretty much. Yeah.

18:07.253 --> 18:10.839
So far.

18:10.840 --> 18:12.799
<i>You pick your way upriver,</i>

18:12.800 --> 18:15.343
<i>like walking up a gradual flight of stairs,</i>

18:15.344 --> 18:18.056
<i>getting out often to push.</i>

18:33.195 --> 18:35.280
<i>With several hours still to go,</i>

18:35.281 --> 18:38.033
<i>a stop for lunch.</i>

18:38.034 --> 18:40.411
There we are.

18:42.121 --> 18:43.872
We're even right on a beach, too.

18:43.873 --> 18:45.665
All right. That's cool.

18:45.666 --> 18:47.709
Looks like bamboo chicken there.

18:47.710 --> 18:51.005
♪

19:05.019 --> 19:07.562
Good.

19:07.563 --> 19:08.647
Good, right?

19:08.648 --> 19:10.023
It's great.

19:10.024 --> 19:13.860
That means delicious.

19:13.861 --> 19:16.362
Yeah, how's your Iban?

19:16.363 --> 19:18.824
It's possible, I guess.

19:18.825 --> 19:20.993
Basic words.

19:20.994 --> 19:24.079
I gather the plan is to try
to get there before dark.

19:24.080 --> 19:25.122
I don't think it's going to happen.

19:25.123 --> 19:26.958
Yeah, me either. No.

19:34.799 --> 19:37.760
♪

19:45.726 --> 19:47.687
Hey!

19:53.567 --> 19:55.653
Hello.

19:58.197 --> 20:00.073
<i>All those years ago</i>

20:00.074 --> 20:02.117
<i>the man who looked after
me at the longhouse</i>

20:02.118 --> 20:04.786
<i>was named Itom.</i>

20:04.787 --> 20:06.746
<i>Over 80 years old back then,</i>

20:06.747 --> 20:09.166
<i>he led us bounding uphill
through the jungle</i>

20:09.167 --> 20:12.002
<i>like a young gazelle.</i>

20:12.003 --> 20:13.795
<i>He still had the marks on his fingers</i>

20:13.796 --> 20:16.381
<i>of a man who'd taken heads,</i>

20:16.382 --> 20:19.092
<i>in his case, presumably communist guerillas</i>

20:19.093 --> 20:20.927
<i>when he'd fought with the British</i>

20:20.928 --> 20:23.388
<i>during the Malay insurgency.</i>

20:23.389 --> 20:29.061
<i>We drank shots of whiskey
together under human skulls,</i>

20:29.062 --> 20:31.521
<i>trophies from another time.</i>

20:31.522 --> 20:33.899
<i>And I promised I'd come back for Gawai,</i>

20:33.900 --> 20:36.193
<i>a big deal in the Iban calendar,</i>

20:36.194 --> 20:41.364
<i>when friends and relatives
return to the longhouse.</i>

20:41.365 --> 20:44.117
<i>A lot has changed since he tracked commies</i>

20:44.118 --> 20:46.285
<i>through the jungle and much has changed</i>

20:46.286 --> 20:49.414
<i>in the ten years since I've been here.</i>

20:49.415 --> 20:53.793
<i>Itom passed away the year
before last at the age of 92,</i>

20:53.794 --> 20:55.879
<i>and the evidence of how timbering</i>

20:55.880 --> 21:01.219
<i>has depleted much of the forest
is everywhere, scandalously so.</i>

21:05.305 --> 21:09.810
♪

21:40.007 --> 21:42.759
<i>It's dark by the time we arrive,</i>

21:42.760 --> 21:46.680
<i>but someone has been waiting for us.</i>

21:49.850 --> 21:52.352
Please advise me of protocol.

22:01.821 --> 22:03.321
Thank you.

22:03.322 --> 22:06.159
All for me.

22:12.581 --> 22:15.959
Oh, yeah. Just like old times.

22:15.960 --> 22:18.461
There you go, my man.

22:18.462 --> 22:20.798
Custom must be observed.

22:23.634 --> 22:24.885
Thank you.

22:30.099 --> 22:32.101
Woo.

22:36.647 --> 22:39.733
♪

23:16.103 --> 23:18.731
More cell phones than last time.

23:19.982 --> 23:22.776
♪

23:49.970 --> 23:51.305
This is a great welcome.

24:04.318 --> 24:05.403
Pardon?

24:06.444 --> 24:07.947
Yes.

24:13.577 --> 24:16.372
My respect, my condolence.

24:22.044 --> 24:25.046
She cannot stand longer. Of course.

24:25.047 --> 24:27.465
Thank you.

24:49.322 --> 24:51.907
♪

25:02.835 --> 25:07.505
<i>Back after a lot of years
and a lot of miles.</i>

25:09.300 --> 25:12.551
<i>I wake up to the sounds of
early morning village life.</i>

25:12.552 --> 25:14.387
<i>Roosters call.</i>

25:14.388 --> 25:16.014
<i>The coughing and clearing of lungs</i>

25:16.015 --> 25:19.476
<i>as the elders rise to do chores.</i>

25:19.477 --> 25:23.438
<i>The whole village lives
here in separate apartment,</i>

25:23.439 --> 25:24.897
<i>sharing a communal space</i>

25:24.898 --> 25:28.776
<i>that runs the length of the building.</i>

25:28.777 --> 25:32.364
<i>Some things have noticeably changed.</i>

25:32.365 --> 25:34.073
<i>The longhouse I first stayed in</i>

25:34.074 --> 25:38.036
<i>has been replaced by a
somewhat more modern version.</i>

25:38.037 --> 25:39.578
<i>These days there's electricity</i>

25:39.579 --> 25:42.790
<i>from a reliable diesel generator.</i>

25:42.791 --> 25:44.167
<i>And while there's no cell phone
signal, the plumbing works,</i>

25:44.168 --> 25:47.628
<i>the washing in the river is still,</i>

25:47.629 --> 25:52.091
<i>the way I see it, anyway,
the preferable option.</i>

25:52.092 --> 25:54.845
♪

26:01.977 --> 26:03.478
<i>In this part of the world,</i>

26:03.479 --> 26:05.938
<i>you live or die by the rice harvest.</i>

26:05.939 --> 26:08.525
<i>Less so these days as
timbering has changed,</i>

26:08.526 --> 26:10.735
<i>well, everything out here,</i>

26:10.736 --> 26:13.863
<i>but traditions run deep
with the Iban, and Gawai,</i>

26:13.864 --> 26:16.824
<i>the harvest festival was and remains like</i>

26:16.825 --> 26:20.538
<i>Christmas and New Year's rolled into one.</i>

26:43.936 --> 26:46.979
<i>We will need pork for Gawai.</i>

26:46.980 --> 26:51.609
<i>And unfortunately, that
means a pig must die.</i>

26:54.196 --> 26:56.197
<i>More awkwardly, custom,</i>

26:56.198 --> 26:57.990
<i>and my personal history
in this village demands,</i>

26:57.991 --> 27:01.828
<i>once again, that I do the job.</i>

27:11.004 --> 27:14.173
<i>"Down by the river, I shot my baby."</i>

27:14.174 --> 27:16.175
<i>What did Neil mean by that?</i>

27:16.176 --> 27:19.137
<i>Why would he do that? Shoot his baby?</i>

27:19.138 --> 27:23.724
<i>Unless baby was a delicious, delicious pig.</i>

27:23.725 --> 27:25.727
♪

28:50.396 --> 28:53.939
<i>I'd like to tell you
that this is never easy,</i>

28:53.940 --> 28:57.860
<i>that I felt this time like
I did the first time.</i>

28:57.861 --> 29:00.946
<i>Sad, nauseated, complicit,</i>

29:00.947 --> 29:02.657
<i>aware that I crossed a line,</i>

29:02.658 --> 29:05.201
<i>been changed by the violence and the blood</i>

29:05.202 --> 29:06.704
<i>and the awful noise.</i>

29:07.954 --> 29:09.831
<i>But that would be a lie.</i>

29:13.377 --> 29:15.836
<i>This time, I plunged the spear in</i>

29:15.837 --> 29:19.299
<i>without hesitation or remorse.</i>

29:37.484 --> 29:41.779
<i>When the pig dies, finally gives it up,</i>

29:41.780 --> 29:45.157
<i>I feel only relief.</i>

29:45.158 --> 29:48.369
<i>I have been hardened by the last ten years.</i>

29:48.370 --> 29:54.376
<i>I don't know what that says
about me, but there it is.</i>

31:03.945 --> 31:05.822
<i>Far up the Skrang river,</i>

31:05.823 --> 31:09.408
<i>the countdown to Gawai is on,</i>

31:09.409 --> 31:12.411
<i>and I can't help but be struck
by one particular upgrade</i>

31:12.412 --> 31:14.580
<i>since my last visit.</i>

31:14.581 --> 31:17.917
♪

31:27.511 --> 31:29.178
<i>Karaoke.</i>

31:29.179 --> 31:31.972
<i>As I come to learn, constant karaoke.</i>

31:31.973 --> 31:34.518
<i>Never-ending karaoke.</i>

31:38.271 --> 31:40.898
<i>From a limited playlist of favorites.</i>

31:40.899 --> 31:43.067
<i>Nearly 24 hours a day</i>

31:43.068 --> 31:45.653
<i>accompanied by copious amounts of beer,</i>

31:45.654 --> 31:48.656
<i>tuak, and other strong spirits.</i>

31:48.657 --> 31:50.200
♪

32:35.495 --> 32:38.539
<i>It should be pointed out
Gawai isn't just about</i>

32:38.540 --> 32:42.042
<i>consuming potentially
blinding amounts of alcohol.</i>

32:42.043 --> 32:44.629
<i>It's also about food.</i>

32:44.630 --> 32:47.298
<i>And one would be well advised to eat a lot.</i>

32:47.299 --> 32:52.094
<i>Lay down a solid base for
the torrent to come.</i>

32:52.095 --> 32:54.179
Oh, thank you.

32:54.180 --> 32:55.723
I feel so guilty.

32:55.724 --> 32:57.308
No, no, not at all, actually.

32:57.309 --> 32:58.768
Should not.

32:58.769 --> 33:00.270
So delicious.

33:03.774 --> 33:06.024
Oh, no, that's good. All right.

33:06.025 --> 33:10.279
That's Iban tradition that
people put rice on their plate.

33:10.280 --> 33:12.407
Common. Yeah, yeah.

33:16.662 --> 33:18.538
Delicious.

34:22.018 --> 34:25.353
Welcome back. I mean, thank you.

34:25.355 --> 34:27.900
Cheers. Cheers.

34:55.092 --> 34:57.762
<i>As the revelry kicks into high gear,</i>

34:57.763 --> 35:01.265
<i>there is nowhere to hide.</i>

35:01.266 --> 35:03.059
<i>I know only that if I sit still</i>

35:03.060 --> 35:05.937
<i>anywhere within range of hospitality,</i>

35:05.938 --> 35:09.356
<i>there will be a river of booze.</i>

35:09.357 --> 35:14.070
<i>Beer, tuak, which is rough
hand-crafted local rice wine</i>

35:14.071 --> 35:18.324
<i>and its more lethal distilled
bigger brother, langkau.</i>

35:20.493 --> 35:25.205
<i>Then somebody's pouring you
Johnny Black or J.D. or Vat 69.</i>

35:25.206 --> 35:27.416
<i>Then langkau again, then who knows?</i>

35:27.417 --> 35:31.169
<i>You only know it keeps coming
until you sag facedown</i>

35:31.170 --> 35:34.256
<i>onto the handwoven mats and pass out.</i>

35:34.257 --> 35:42.257
<i>Perfectly acceptable practice, by the way.</i>

35:44.309 --> 35:46.478
Bring me back to paradise.

35:52.484 --> 35:56.445
<i>I wake up, I go to sleep, I wake up again.</i>

35:56.446 --> 36:00.491
<i>The party has moved down a few
doors, but it's still going.</i>

36:00.492 --> 36:05.037
<i>This is an experience that will
repeat itself again and again</i>

36:05.038 --> 36:07.582
<i>for the next three days.</i>

36:11.461 --> 36:13.838
<i>One time it's the ladies still standing,</i>

36:13.839 --> 36:18.968
<i>partying like it's 1999,
dancing and drinking,</i>

36:18.969 --> 36:20.845
<i>and another time it's the old dudes,</i>

36:20.846 --> 36:24.431
<i>the village chiefs and elders,</i>

36:24.432 --> 36:27.601
<i>and everybody, elders, women, children,</i>

36:27.602 --> 36:30.395
<i>visiting relatives and their
families from Kuala Lumpur</i>

36:30.396 --> 36:31.897
<i>Puchong and abroad.</i>

36:31.898 --> 36:36.485
<i>Wherever circumstances took them.</i>

36:36.486 --> 36:38.780
Ba, ba, ba.

36:39.781 --> 36:41.490
<i>The party expands and contracts</i>

36:41.491 --> 36:43.325
<i>according to mysterious patterns</i>

36:43.326 --> 36:46.454
<i>that I am in no shape to discern.</i>

36:55.463 --> 36:57.340
One, two, three...

37:12.856 --> 37:14.439
<i>Morning routine.</i>

37:14.440 --> 37:16.859
<i>Wake up, feed the chickens,</i>

37:16.860 --> 37:19.570
<i>rake the pepper drying in the sun,</i>

37:19.571 --> 37:23.323
<i>then it's time to rock the bike, people,</i>

37:23.324 --> 37:26.952
<i>and it starts all over again.</i>

37:26.953 --> 37:29.748
♪

37:35.587 --> 37:39.882
<i>While the party continues
up at the longhouse,</i>

37:39.883 --> 37:47.883
<i>I've got an appointment.</i>

38:02.864 --> 38:05.574
<i>If you were wondering, by
the way, if this hurts,</i>

38:05.575 --> 38:07.534
<i>two guys hammering away at my sternum</i>

38:07.535 --> 38:09.995
<i>with a bamboo club, sharp needles?</i>

38:09.996 --> 38:12.998
<i>Yes, yes, it hurt a lot.</i>

38:12.999 --> 38:16.376
<i>And you could be damn sure
if it was not on television,</i>

38:16.377 --> 38:21.258
<i>I'd be whimpering and yelping
like a gutshot poodle.</i>

38:28.389 --> 38:32.017
Right. There, stand up.

38:32.018 --> 38:34.187
All right, good? Very
happy guys, thank you.

38:42.570 --> 38:46.740
All right, let's party.

38:46.741 --> 38:49.743
<i>Another tattoo is never
going to make me younger,</i>

38:49.744 --> 38:51.912
<i>or tougher or more relevant.</i>

38:51.913 --> 38:54.748
<i>It won't reconnect me ten years from now</i>

38:54.749 --> 38:57.751
<i>with some spiritual crossroads in my life.</i>

38:57.752 --> 39:01.964
<i>No. At this point I think</i>

39:01.965 --> 39:04.175
<i>my body is like an old car,</i>

39:04.176 --> 39:08.679
<i>another dent ain't gonna make
a whole lot of difference.</i>

39:08.680 --> 39:12.099
<i>At best, it's a reminder
that you're still alive</i>

39:12.100 --> 39:15.519
<i>and lucky as hell.</i>

39:15.520 --> 39:19.397
<i>Another tattoo, another thing you did,</i>

39:19.398 --> 39:21.359
<i>another place you've been.</i>

39:27.532 --> 39:30.534
<i>A final, long gaze at the river.</i>

39:30.535 --> 39:34.121
<i>Take in, probably for the
last time in my life,</i>

39:34.122 --> 39:37.375
<i>the slow rhythms of the village.</i>

39:43.882 --> 39:45.507
<i>One more thing to do,</i>

39:45.508 --> 39:48.426
<i>say good-bye to an old friend.</i>

39:48.427 --> 39:51.348
♪

40:05.987 --> 40:08.197
He was a very strong man. Yes.

40:08.198 --> 40:14.912
I remember him well running
uphill, faster than all of us.

40:14.913 --> 40:16.413
So what do we do?

40:16.414 --> 40:18.623
We leave him the beer, some cigarettes?

40:18.624 --> 40:20.167
Yes. He would like that?

40:20.168 --> 40:21.752
Yeah, he'd like.

40:21.753 --> 40:23.462
♪

40:33.306 --> 40:36.101
First cigarette in two years for you, man.

